<SECOND>AM-Anti-Semitism Report,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>ADL Reports Upswing in Israel-Related Anti-Semitism</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 There has been a sharp rise in anti-Semitic incidents that stem from opposition to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Anti-Defamation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> of B'nai B'rith reported Tuesday. So far this year, 88 out of 443 anti-Semitic incidents reported in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> have had an element of anti-Israeli sentiment, according to a report by the <ORGANIZATION> ADL </ORGANIZATION>, which monitors outbreaks of racism and anti-Semitism. By contrast, there were only three such incidents out of 1,018 anti-Semitic episodes reported for all of last year. This year's anti-Israeli incidents appeared to be prompted by Palestinian unrest in the occupied territories, the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> ADL </ORGANIZATION> report said. <PERSON> Abraham </PERSON> <PERSON> Foxman </PERSON>, the group's national director, said the incidents represented `` the first time since the founding of the state of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> 40 years ago that there has been a significant outbreak of Middle East-related anti-Semitic incidents in this country.'' The incidents included vandalism and arson attacks on synagogues, telephone threats to Jewish organizations and other forms of verbal harassment. <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> led all states in reports of politically motivated anti-Semitism with 12 vandalism cases and 13 harassment incidents, followed by <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> ADL </ORGANIZATION> said. The figures are based on reports gathered by the <ORGANIZATION> ADL </ORGANIZATION>'s 31 regional offices.
