<HEAD>Elderly Catholic Bishop Released From Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An 80-year-old Roman Catholic bishop jailed since 1982 for ordaining priests outside of the official Communist-controlled church has been released, an official said today. Bishop Fan Xueyan, also known as <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Fan </PERSON>, was released two or three months ago from the <LOCATION> Shijiazhuang </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jail </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Hebei </LOCATION> province, just south of <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>, a <ORGANIZATION> Hebei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> official said in response to a question. The official gave his name only as <PERSON> Li </PERSON>. He said he did not know why <PERSON> Fan </PERSON> was released, his present whereabouts or the state of his health. The <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> ordained Fan bishop of <LOCATION> Baoding </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Hebei </LOCATION> province in 1951, shortly before <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s new Communist government ordered the Chinese Catholic church to break with the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> in the name of anti-imperialism. The officially sanctioned <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patriotic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> that was then formed rejects the authority of the pope and ordains its own bishops. Hundreds of <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> clerics and laypeople who refused to support the association were arrested in the 1950s and many have been released only in the past 10 years. Fan, among them, was arrested in 1958 and spent 15 years in jail. He was arrested again in 1982 and sentenced to 10 years in jail for allegedly maintaining ties with the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> and ordaining priests. The government, which under senior leader <PERSON> Deng </PERSON> <PERSON> Xiaoping </PERSON> has alternated between relaxation and severity in its policy toward religious dissidents, has shown leniency this year to several elder