store near <PERSON> Corinne </PERSON>, and the two other guards were locked inside by a wedge of wood used to jam the door. <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> is charged with three federal felony counts: theft by an agent of the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, theft of bank funds and theft from an interstate shipment. <PERSON> Lund </PERSON> said he did not know why the guard turned himself in, but suggested that a nagging conscience probably was a factor. `` No. 1, he does n't have a criminal history. No. 2, I think he probably planned this thing out and said, ` Yeah, I can live without my family for a while. I can go to <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> ... live luxuriously for a long, long time,''' he said. `` Then he just got to missing these people. I think he might have had some conscience pangs,'' <PERSON> Lund </PERSON> said.
