<TEXT>
 Videos reviewed this week: `` Fatal Attraction'' and `` The Principal.'' `` Fatal Attraction'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION>; VHS, $ 89.95; Beat, $ 29.95; Rated R -RRB- Consummate yuppie <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Gallagher </PERSON> has it all: beautiful wife, adorable daughter, upward mobility, <ORGANIZATION> Volvo </ORGANIZATION> station wagon. He's not looking for a one-night stand, but when it presents itself in the person of sultry publishing exec <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> <PERSON> Forrest </PERSON>, he ca n't resist. How could he know that under those tousled blond locks and <ORGANIZATION> Maybelline </ORGANIZATION> eyes lurks the collective anger, frustration and vengeance of every woman who has ever been done and dumped? Tsk, tsk, <PERSON> Dan </PERSON>. Should've kept your pants on. Played with schizophrenic aplomb by <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Close </PERSON>, <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> answers <PERSON> Dan </PERSON>'s rejection with a series of cruel, creepy antics designed to make your teeth hurt right up to the last second. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON>' <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> elicits little sympathy; there's a distinct feeling he deserves some of what he's getting. <PERSON> Anne </PERSON> <PERSON> Archer </PERSON> as <PERSON> Dan </PERSON>'s wife is so sweetly unknowing that the audience actually ends up feeling guilty on behalf of her adulterous, egocentric cad of a husband Director <PERSON> Adrian </PERSON> `` Flashdance'' <PERSON> Lyne </PERSON> knows how to create and build tension: no surprise that this slick production was last year's second-highest grossing movie. As the `` R'' rating indicates, there's a little too much sex, flesh and violence for the kiddies. Otherwise, `` Fatal Attraction'' is a peach of a psychological thriller that could make even the most dedicated couch potato squirm. _ By <PERSON> Lisa </PERSON> <PER