</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 `` The Principal'' -LRB- RCA @ <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> Home Video; VHS @ Beta, $ 89.95; Rated R -RRB- In `` The Principal,'' <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Belushi </PERSON> plays a Rambo-like high school teacher who drinks too much, smashes Porsches with baseball bats and generally ticks off his bosses at the stuffy old board of education. Instead of firing him, they decide to `` reward'' him with a principalship. Trouble is, it's at <ORGANIZATION> Brandel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>, the low-down dirtiest, most crime-infested, drug-ridden school on the planet. The film misses no opportunity for gratuitous violence. The kids do n't just taunt or ignore him _ they beat him to a bloody pulp. The teachers are assaulted. And in finest spaghetti Western fashion, <PERSON> Belushi </PERSON>, riding his motorcycle into the very halls of Brandel, is going to tame this here school, pard-ner. There is a climactic chase scene and showdown in the girl's shower _ this film's ludicrous version of the OK Corral Even a graduate of Brandel could predict the outcome of this absurd, boring, exploitative movie. And even a better actor than <PERSON> Belushi </PERSON> could have done little with such pea-brained dialogue as this sample when he tries to inspire downtrodden teachers: `` Aw, come on, you people,'' says he, his voice rising Patton-like. `` You ca n't pick and choose your students.'' The film also features <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Gossett </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, muttering unintelligible cynicisms as the school's security guard. Tough schools lately seem to have caught <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>'s fancy. Unfortunately, it is only the rare film, such as the excellent `` Stand and Deliver,'' that manages not to succumb to sexploitation or racist, blackboard jungle caricatures. `` The Principal,'' rated `` R,'' contains the foul, street-language you'd expect in a film such as this. But not to worry. The rest of the dialogue will probably put you to sleep. _ By <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitgang </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> Education Writer.
