<HEAD>USAir Reports Cancellations Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION>'s schedules were disrupted again Tuesday as some flight attendants continued to refuse to work overtime in apparent protest of an impasse in contract negotiations. The airline, based in <LOCATION> Arlington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, canceled 24 flights in its first eight hours of operation Tuesday, said spokesman <PERSON> Dave </PERSON> <PERSON> Shipley </PERSON>. `` It's a very, very small percentage of the total,'' <PERSON> Shipley </PERSON> said. `` There's not chaos at the airports.'' <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> schedules about 1,600 flights daily, <PERSON> Shipley </PERSON> said. He said <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> canceled one flight Saturday, 81 flights Sunday and 61 flights Monday. An impasse in contract negotiations between <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Flight </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Attendants </ORGANIZATION> apparently prompted the airline's flight attendants to decline overtime <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> has yet to complete an agreement for a new contract and seniority list with its flight attendants and those employed by <ORGANIZATION> Pacific </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, which was acquired by <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> last year and merged into <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION>'s system April 9. `` Apparently there is -LRB- a protest -RRB-, but it's not a union-organized protest. I think it's a spontaneous protest. I was as surprised as anyone else,'' said <PERSON> Juliette </PERSON> <PERSON> Lenoir </PERSON>, vice president of the <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, D.C.-based union and a <ORGANIZATION> USAir </ORGANIZATION> flight attendant. `` My best sense is that flight attendants are just very upset at this whole issue of pay parity for the former <ORGANIZATION> PSA </ORGANIZ