 <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lines </ORGANIZATION> is going after kiddie flyers, announcing Tuesday an expanded youth fare program for the summer to go along with a previously announced prize program for children to fly along with `` <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lion </ORGANIZATION>.'' The reduced fare will be in effect systemwide, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> said, more than doubling the number of markets in which the fare is available. <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> already had matched youth fares announced May 16 by <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> airlines in areas where it competed with the three. Delta, the nation's fourth largest airline, said the youth fares and a `` Fantastic Flyer'' program take effect Wednesday. The fares give children ages 2 through 17 who travel through Sept. 11 a special price when accompanied by adults who have purchased a non-refundable fare. One child may accompany each adult, following the same advance purchase and minimum stay rules in force with the adult's fare. The airline, which already has a marketing tie-in with <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> near <LOCATION> Orlan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, expects most of the fares to include <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. For example, round-trip fares from cities east of the <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> will be $ 97 on weekends and $ 77 for midweek travel. For travel from cities west of the <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, or between two cities outside the state of <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, the fares will be limited to midweek and are based of a mileage formula ranging from $ 58 to $ 198. Under the Fantastic Flyer program announced last week, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> will give prizes and other rewards to children between 2 and 12 years old. Calling Delta `` The Official Airline for Kids,'' <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> senior vice president <PERSON> Whit </PERSON> <PERSON> Hawkins </PERSON> said, `` On every <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> flight, children will receive a complimentary <PERSON> Mickey </PERSON> <PERSON> Mouse </PERSON> visor ... a copy of the Fantastic Flyer Magazine featuring games, puzzles, stories and prizes created just for them.'' <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Lundy </PERSON> said the airline is after two groups of travelers, with its lower fares and Fantastic Flyer gambits: vacationers making trips with their children and unaccompanied children.
